OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774725064
OL,3,CGovernment must apologise for historic
OL,4,Cforced adoption, MPs say
OL,6,FIn his evidence to the committee, Mr
OL,7,FMacAlister said he accepted "the state
OL,8,Fhad a role" in "a practice that went
OL,9,Fon for decades, forcibly removing
OL,10,Fchildren from these women in homes
OL,11,Fthat were sometimes run by the state,
OL,12,Fenabled and overseen by social workers
OL,13,Femployed by the state, and social
OL,14,Fattitudes that were reinforced by
OL,15,Fpractices that carried on for many
OL,16,Fyears".
OL,26,@oD@]OUpD@KO]pD@POUxD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/21
