OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774725064
OL,3,CGovernment must apologise for historic
OL,4,Cforced adoption, MPs say
OL,6,FMs Hayes said an apology must be co-
OL,7,Fproduced with survivors, "ensuring it
OL,8,Freflects their experiences, and it
OL,9,Fshould commit to offer survivors
OL,10,Fmeaningful support beyond the apology
OL,11,Fitself, including better access to
OL,12,Frecords, trauma-informed healthcare
OL,13,Fand regular consultation with the
OL,14,Fgovernment".
OL,26,@oD@ZOUvD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/21
