OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1774725064
OL,3,CGovernment must apologise for historic
OL,4,Cforced adoption, MPs say
OL,6,FThe review urged that a trauma-
OL,7,Finformed health pathway for all those
OL,8,Faffected should be developed,
OL,9,Fincluding improved access to
OL,10,Fpsychological support and national
OL,11,Fclinical guidance recognising the
OL,12,Fheightened prevalence of complex post
OL,13,Ftraumatic stress disorder (PTSD) and
OL,14,Fsuicide risk among survivors.
OL,16,FA government spokesperson told ITV
OL,17,FNews: "This abhorrent practice should
OL,18,Fnever have taken place, and our
OL,19,Fdeepest sympathies are with all those
OL,20,Faffected.
